\newlabel{fig:spread_characterisation}{{5.2}{22}{Spread characterisation summary for the two cointegrated pairs (January 2019 -- December 2023). (a) Half-life of mean reversion in trading days; dashed line marks the 60-day threshold. (b) Hurst exponent; dashed line marks the random walk boundary of 0.5. (c) Current $z$-score at the end of the training window; dotted lines mark $\pm 2\sigma $. (d) ADF $p$-value on the spread; dashed line marks the 5\% significance level. Hatched bars indicate pairs that fail the respective threshold}{figure.5.2}{}}
